'''Patrick Pentz''' (born 2 January 1997) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Danish Superliga]] club [[Brøndby IF|Brøndby]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fk-austria.at/spieler/patrick-pentz|title=FK Austria Wien - Patrick Pentz|publisher=[[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]]|access-date=12 May 2022|archive-date=8 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220508155316/https://fk-austria.at/spieler/patrick-pentz|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Austria Wien===
[[File:20161203 ADM AUS 3873.jpg|thumb|150px|left|Pentz with [[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]] in 2016.]]
Pentz played youth football at SV Bürmoos in the state of Salzburg before joining [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]'s academy in 2006.<ref name="News">{{cite news |title=Patrick Pentz: Sicherer Rückhalt im ÖFB-Team |url=https://www.news.at/menschen/patrick-pentz |access-date=9 November 2025 |work=News.at |date=19 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250807131732/https://www.news.at/menschen/patrick-pentz |archive-date=7 August 2025 |language=de |trans-title=Patrick Pentz: A reliable presence in the Austria national team}}</ref> He moved to [[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]] in 2013 and was first listed with the club's [[Austrian Regionalliga|Regionalliga]] squad that August, making his debut for [[FK Austria Wien II|Austria Wien II]] in September 2014. He received his first senior call-up in April 2015 and, with both first-choice goalkeepers unavailable, made his [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] debut on the final matchday of the 2015–16 season: a 3–0 win over [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] on 15 May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heute.at/sport/fussball/bundesliga/Austria-Wien-gewinnt-Abschiedsspiel-in-Generali-Arena;art56243,1288743|title=3:0 über Sturm Graz: Austria Wien gewinnt Abschiedsspiel in Generali Arena|first=DJ Digitale Medien|last=GmbH.|publisher=|access-date=27 February 2017|archive-date=27 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227154700/http://www.heute.at/sport/fussball/bundesliga/Austria-Wien-gewinnt-Abschiedsspiel-in-Generali-Arena;art56243,1288743|url-status=dead}}</ref>

From the [[2017–18 FK Austria Wien season|2017–18 season]], he established himself as Austria Wien's starting goalkeeper, aside from a brief spell during the 2019–20 season, when [[Ivan Lučić (footballer, born 1995)|Ivan Lučić]] held the position, and totalled 129 Bundesliga appearances for the club. He was voted the league's best goalkeeper in both the [[2020–21 Austrian Football Bundesliga|2020–21]] and [[2021–22 Austrian Football Bundesliga|2021–22 seasons]].<ref name="team21" /><ref name="team22" /> After nine years with Austria Wien, he left at the end of the 2021–22 campaign.<ref>{{cite press release |title=Danke, Patrick Pentz! |url=https://fk-austria.at/news/danke-patrick-pentz |website=FK Austria Wien |access-date=9 November 2025 |language=de |date=15 June 2022 |trans-title=Thank you, Patrick Pentz!}}</ref>

===Reims===
On 9 July 2022, Pentz signed a three-year contract with [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] in [[Ligue 1]].<ref name="stade-de-reims.com">{{cite web |title=Patrick Pentz : un nouveau shérif en ville |url=https://www.stade-de-reims.com/patrick-pentz-un-nouveau-sherif-en-ville/ |website=Stade de Reims |date=9 July 2022 |access-date=10 July 2022 |language=fr}}</ref> He began the [[2022–23 Ligue 1|2022–23]] season as first-choice goalkeeper before later losing the position to [[Yehvann Diouf]].<ref name="stade-de-reims.com"/>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
On 27 January 2023, Pentz joined [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen]] on a two-and-a-half-year deal.<ref name="bayer04.de">{{cite web |title=Lunev injured – Bayer 04 sign Austria keeper Pentz |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/lunev-injured-bayer-04-sign-austria-keeper-pentz |website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |date=27 January 2023 |access-date=27 January 2023}}</ref> Serving as back-up to [[Lukáš Hrádecký]], he did not make a first-team appearance for the club.<ref name="bayer04.de"/>

=== Brøndby ===
On 18 August 2023, Pentz joined [[Brøndby IF|Brøndby]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=Brøndby IF indgår lejekontrakt med Patrick Pentz |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2023/august/brondby-if-indgar-lejekontrakt-med-patrick-pentz |website=Brøndby IF |date=18 August 2023 |access-date=18 August 2023 |language=da |trans-title=Brøndby IF enter into a loan agreement with Patrick Pentz}}</ref> He made his competitive debut ten days later, starting and keeping a clean sheet in a 1–0 away win over [[Vejle Boldklub]] in the [[Danish Superliga]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sejr over Vejle Boldklub |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2023/august/sejr-over-vejle-boldklub |website=Brøndby IF |date=28 August 2023 |access-date=9 November 2025 |language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Vejle Boldklub - Brøndby IF |url=https://brondbystats.dk/Match/Details/3516 |website=BrøndbyStats |date=28 August 2023 |access-date=9 November 2025 |language=da}}</ref> He remained first choice for the remainder of the season, recording 11 clean sheets in 30 competitive appearances in league and cup.<ref name="SW">{{cite web |title=Patrick Pentz profile |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/patrick-pentz/325212/ |website=Soccerway |access-date=9 November 2025}}</ref>

On 10 June 2024, Brøndby made the transfer permanent and Pentz signed a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Four more years – Brøndby IF og Patrick Pentz forlænger |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/klub/2024/juni/four-more-years-brondby-if-og-patrick-pentz-forlaenger |website=Brøndby IF |date=10 June 2024 |access-date=10 June 2024 |language=da}}</ref> During the same window he was also linked in the media with interest from [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]], [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] and [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Okstrøm |first=Oliver |title=Pentz om rygte: Brøndby er den eneste klub for mig |url=https://www.tipsbladet.dk/nyhed/superliga/pentz-om-rygte-broendby-er-den-eneste-klub-mig |work=Tipsbladet |date=15 May 2024 |access-date=9 November 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240523102338/https://www.tipsbladet.dk/nyhed/superliga/pentz-om-rygte-broendby-er-den-eneste-klub-mig |archive-date=23 May 2024 |language=da |trans-title=Pentz on rumours: Brøndby is the only club for me}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Glud |first=Rasmus |title=Celtic og Southampton var med i ræset om Pentz |url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/klubber/broendby-if/nyheder/celtic-og-southampton-var-med-i-raeset-om-pentz |work=Bold |date=10 June 2024 |access-date=9 November 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241004011528/https://bold.dk/fodbold/klubber/broendby-if/nyheder/celtic-og-southampton-var-med-i-raeset-om-pentz |archive-date=4 October 2024 |language=da |trans-title=Celtic and Southampton were in the race for Pentz}}</ref> On 7 December 2024 he was named Brøndby's Player of the Year for 2024.<ref>{{cite web |title=Patrick Pentz er årets spiller 2024 |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2024/december/patrick-pentz-er-arets-spiller-2024 |website=Brøndby IF |date=7 December 2024 |access-date=9 November 2025 |language=da}}</ref> Later that month he was named Danish Goalkeeper of the Year, winning ''[[Tipsbladet]]'s [[Det Gyldne Bur]]'' for 2024—an award voted on by the first-choice goalkeepers in the Superliga and [[Danish 1st Division|1st Division]].<ref name="DGB" />

On 13 April 2025, after a 2–1 away win against Copenhagen at [[Parken Stadium]], Pentz was shown a second yellow card for unsporting behaviour during the post-match celebrations. A melee ensued in which Copenhagen goalkeeper [[Diant Ramaj]] and Brøndby reserve [[Thomas Mikkelsen (footballer, born 1983)|Thomas Mikkelsen]] were also dismissed; Ramaj was later reported to have head-butted Mikkelsen. [[Thomas Delaney]] criticised Pentz's conduct in a post-match interview.<ref>{{cite news |title=Delaney om Pentz: Det udviser mangel på respekt |url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/nyheder/delaney-om-pentz-det-udviser-mangel-pa-respekt/  |work=Bold |date=13 April 2025 |access-date=9 November 2025 |language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Drama i Danmark – nu er der nyt |url=https://www.tipsbladet.dk/nyhed/superliga/drama-i-danmark-nu-er-der-nyt |work=Tipsbladet |date=2 October 2025 |access-date=9 November 2025 |language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Brøndby appellerer rødt kort til målmand |url=https://www.tv3sport.dk/sport/fodbold/nyheder/medie-brondby-appellerer-rodt-kort-til-malmand |website=TV 3 SPORT |date=April 2025 |access-date=9 November 2025 |language=da}}</ref>

==International career==
Pentz represented Austria at the U17, U18 and U21 levels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oefb.at/10erfolg-im-freundschaftlichen-news23933|title=ÖFB|first=ÖFB - Österreichischer|last=Fußballbund|publisher=|access-date=27 February 2017|archive-date=27 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227150340/http://www.oefb.at/10erfolg-im-freundschaftlichen-news23933|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut for the [[Austria national football team|senior national team]] on 29 March 2022, coming on as a substitute in the friendly match against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Roundup: Elf Austrianer international unterwegs |url=https://fk-austria.at/news/roundup-elf-austrianer-international-unterwegs |publisher=[[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]] |access-date=12 May 2022 |language=de |date=30 March 2022}}</ref>

